1
00:00:01,418 --> 00:00:04,379
CASS: Help me, please.
Can anybody hear me?

2
00:00:04,463 --> 00:00:06,798
COMPUTER: Please state the nature
of your ailment or injury.

3
00:00:06,924 --> 00:00:09,676
I'm not injured. I'm crashing.
I don't need a doctor.

4
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,054
COMPUTER: A clear statement
of your symptoms will help us provide

5
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:16,308
the medical practitioner appropriate
to your individual needs.

6
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:19,561
I'm trying to send a distress signal.
Stop talking about doctors.

7
00:00:19,645 --> 00:00:21,897
MAN: I'm a doctor.

8
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,442
But probably not
the one you were expecting.

9
00:00:26,944 --> 00:00:28,946
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

10
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:42,543
-Where are the rest of the crew?
-Teleported off.

11
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,545
-But you're still here?
- Iteleported them.

12
00:00:44,628 --> 00:00:46,380
-Why you?
-Everyone else was screaming.

13
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:49,633
-Welcome aboard.
-Aboard what?

14
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,593
I'll show you.

15
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:55,013
Where are we going?

16
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:56,348
-Back of the ship.
-Why?

17
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:58,684
Because the front crashes first.
Think it through.

18
00:00:58,809 --> 00:01:01,019
Oh, why did you do that?

19
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,771
-Emergency protocols.
-(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

20
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:04,606
-What's your name?
-Cass.

21
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:06,775
You're young to be
crewing a gunship, Cass.

22
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:09,820
I wanted to see the universe.
Is it always like this?

23
00:01:09,945 --> 00:01:12,197
If you're lucky.

24
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:17,244
-Don't worry. It's bigger on the inside.
-What did you say?

25
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:19,413
"Bigger on the inside"?
Is that what you said?

26
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:22,207
-Yes. Come on, you'll love it.
-Is this a Tardis?

27
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,418
Yes, but you'll be perfectly safe,
I promise you.

28
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:28,130
-Don't touch me!
-I'm not part of the war.

29
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:30,257
I swear to you, I never was.

30
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:32,593
-You're a Time Lord.
-Yes, I'm a Time Lord.

31
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:35,721
-But I'm one of the nice ones.
-Get away from me.

32
00:01:35,846 --> 00:01:37,556
Well, look on the bright side.
I'm not a Dalek!

33
00:01:37,681 --> 00:01:40,601
Who can tell the difference any more?

34
00:01:40,684 --> 00:01:43,854
-Cass!
-It's deadlocked. Don't even try.

35
00:01:43,979 --> 00:01:46,189
Cass, just open the door.
I'm trying to help.

36
00:01:46,315 --> 00:01:49,276
Go back to your battlefield.

37
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:53,238
You haven't finished yet. (SOBS)
Some of the universe is still standing.

38
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:57,367
-I'm not leaving this ship without you.
-Then you're gonna die right there.

39
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:01,455
-Best news all day.
-Cass. Cass.

40
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:04,207
(SHOUTS) Cass!

41
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:07,377
Cass! Cass!

42
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:16,345
And here he is at last,

43
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:18,555
the man to end it all.

44
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:22,559
My sisters,
the Doctor has returned to Karn.

45
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:25,354
PRIESTESS: We have always known
in our bones

46
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:28,106
that one day he would return here.

47
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:31,026
Such a pity he's dead.

48
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:39,951
Cass!

49
00:02:41,244 --> 00:02:43,205
If you refer to your companion,

50
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:45,374
we are still attempting
to extract her from the wreckage.

51
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:48,710
-She wasn't my companion.
-She's almost certainly dead.

52
00:02:48,794 --> 00:02:51,254
-No one could survive that crash.
-I did.

53
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:53,882
No, we restored you to life.

54
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:58,845
But it's a temporary measure.
You have a little under four minutes.

55
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:01,473
Four minutes? That's ages.

56
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:04,142
What if I get bored?
I need a television. Couple of books.

57
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:06,103
Anyone for chess? Bring me knitting.

58
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:10,065
You have so little breath left.
Spend it wisely.

59
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,902
Hang on, is it you?

60
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:17,572
Am I back on Karn?

61
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:20,158
You're the Sisterhood of Karn.

62
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:23,203
Keepers of the Flame of Utter Boredom.

63
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,580
-"Eternal Life".
-That's the one.

64
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:28,083
Mock us if you will, but our elixir

65
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:31,002
can trigger your regeneration,
bring you back.

66
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:35,173
Time Lord science is elevated
here on Karn.

67
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:37,175
The change doesn't have to be random.

68
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:42,806
Fat or thin, young or old,
man or woman.

69
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:46,977
-Why would you do this for me?
-You have helped us in the past.

70
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:49,813
You were never big on gratitude.

71
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,691
The war between the Daleks and
the Time Lords threatens all reality.

72
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,985
You are the only hope left.

73
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:57,571
It's not my war.
I will have no part of it.

74
00:03:57,654 --> 00:04:02,117
-You can't ignore it forever.
-I help where I can. I will not fight.

75
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,161
Because you are "the good man",
as you call yourself?

76
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:08,248
-I call myself the Doctor.
-It's the same thing, in your mind.

77
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:11,168
-I'd like to think so.
-In that case, Doctor,

78
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:15,505
attend your patient.

79
00:04:21,845 --> 00:04:24,264
-(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)
-PRIESTESS: You're wasting your time.

80
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,600
She is beyond even our help.

81
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:29,895
-She wanted to see the universe.
-She didn't miss much.

82
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,646
It's very nearly over.

83
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:34,441
I could have saved her. I could have
got her off there. She wouldn't listen.

84
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:35,984
Then she was wiser than you.

85
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,445
She understood there was no escaping
the Time War.

86
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:41,865
You are a part of this, Doctor,
whether you like it or not.

87
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:44,701
-I would rather die.
-You're dead already.

88
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,995
How many more will you let join you?

89
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:51,374
If she could speak,

90
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:55,003
-what would she say?
-To me? Nothing.

91
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:58,256
I'm a Time Lord.
Everything she despised.

92
00:04:58,924 --> 00:05:02,594
She would beg your help,
as we beg your help now.

93
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:08,058
The universe stands on the brink.
Will you let it fall?

94
00:05:09,893 --> 00:05:14,689
Fast or strong? Wise or angry?
What do you need now?

95
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:21,404
-Warrior.
-Warrior?

96
00:05:22,531 --> 00:05:25,200
I don't suppose there's any need
for a Doctor any more.

97
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:28,870
Make me a Warrior, now.

98
00:05:28,954 --> 00:05:31,915
I took the liberty
of preparing this one myself.

99
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:36,753
Get out. Get out!

100
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:39,923
All of you.

101
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,595
-Will it hurt?
-Yes.

102
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,430
Good.

103
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:52,644
Charley, C'rizz, Lucie, Tamsin, Molly,

104
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:56,606
friends, companions I've known,
I salute you.

105
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,775
Cass...

106
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,610
I apologise.

107
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:06,116
"Physician, heal thyself."

108
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,842
Argh! (GROANS)

109
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,476
Is it done?

110
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:55,290
WAR DOCTOR: "Doctor" no more.

